# The Compilation and Build Process in C

---

## 1. Overview of the Build Process

In the industry, the entire journey from source code to a running program is often referred to as the **Build Process**.

It consists of **two primary stages**:

### Stage 1: Compilation

**Converting** programmer-understandable code (**C source code**) into machine-understandable code (**Object Code**).

### Stage 2: Linking

**Connecting** various object code files and libraries into a single **Executable Code**.

---

## Build Process Flow Diagram

```
┌─────────────────┐
│  C Source Code  │
│   (program.c)   │
└────────┬────────┘
         │
         ▼
    ┌────────┐
    │COMPILER│ ← Compilation Time
    └────┬───┘
         │ Performs:
         │ • Syntax Analysis
         │ • Semantic Analysis
         ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│  Object Code    │
